# EC2 — the virtual server

**Elastic Compute Cloud** — AWS's virtual server and most fundamental compute primitive. Almost everything runs on it.

## What an instance is

A **virtual machine**: AWS picks the hardware + hypervisor, you get a slice. You choose the **OS, CPU, memory, storage, network**.

## Six decisions to launch

- **AMI** — the disk image to boot
- **Instance type** — the size
- **Key pair** — to log in
- **Network** — a VPC + public IP
- **Security group** — firewall (open 80, 22)
- **User data** — boot script → running app

## Where this module goes

One instance → **load balancer** in front of many → **Auto Scaling Group** that grows/shrinks the fleet.
